From 2e442a7609580dd83d755c226e4b3323f5a28715 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 11:32:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add support for 'alternate' roots for tegra CSV handling

So the host OS can provide one or more trees of libraries that
should be mounted into containers, overriding the copies in
the main rootfs of the host OS.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]
Signed-off-by: Matt Madison <matt@madison.systems>
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
 api/config/v1/runtime.go                    |  3 +-
 api/config/v1/toml_test.go                  |  2 +
 cmd/nvidia-ctk/cdi/generate/generate.go     |  8 +++
 internal/platform-support/tegra/csv.go      | 64 ++++++++++++++++-----
 internal/platform-support/tegra/options.go  | 13 ++++-
 internal/platform-support/tegra/symlinks.go | 43 ++++++++------
